postcontent:
Up for sale is this WWII vintage ( 1944 I believe ) Springfield Armory M1 Garand. This came from the CMP and is a Service Grade which was a better grade rifle than their Rack or Field grades. Those that are familiar with their codes will see   in one pic I have of the certificate and grade tag.  I have many other pics  other than those shown that I’ll be happy to email upon request. Though I do not have TE or MW gauges I do have a pic of “ the muzzle test “ which it passes with flying colors with a round of  Spec .30 Ball.  The bore is shiny with strong rifling. The rifle was rebuilt by Govt. Arsenal in the middle ‘60’s  ( written on a receiver leg as I recall but due to my age disassembly and reassembly is difficult for me and I will no longer do it so what pics of parts you see will be it ) . The metal parkerizing is in very good cond. The parts pics that I could capture indicate some SA and it has “ NM “ ( National Match ? ) stamped on the Op rod. The front sight / gas cylinder was never removed  since leaving the CMP , is snug on the BBL. so the splines should be pristine.  The wood is strong and solid but has numerous scratches, dings, dents, etc.  The stock has several cartouches.  Though I have had it for several years I did not shoot it much but I can give you my word that it never malfunctioned in any way for me and is very accurate. It was always used with top quality, CMP sold, .30 Ball ammo.  It was always disassembled, cleaned and lubed per spec after every shooting session. I do strongly suggest that the new owner do this upon ownership before firing as it hasn’t been fired in a few years. Feel free to ask me any questions. I may or may not be able to answer them but they will be honest.  I do however pretty much know this rifle inside and out. Again.. I have more pics I can email upon request with an E address. Comes with CMP Certificate, tag and manual. Ad says no shipping but I will ship. No local pickup.   Many online sales references available.
 
This must go to an FFL  ( It is C&R eligible )  . No PO boxes and only to those locations that can legally be shipped to. No Exceptions.  So know your laws prior to buying. No local pickup. Payment must me made by USPS money order ONLY.  Shipping will be $40 which includes insurance, Adult Signature and a UPS tracking #.   I strive to pack things very well with lots of protection and where possible to double the cardboard but if you want to ship me your hard case to pack it in that’s up to you.  I communicate throughout and ship promptly.
